---
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>TailorDost - For Boutique Owners</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@100..900&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/reveal.js@5.1.0/dist/reveal.css"
    />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/reveal.js@5.1.0/dist/theme/white.css"
    />
    <style>
      :root {
        --td-primary: #b8006e;
        --td-primary-light: #c93db3;
        --td-dark: #1d1e33;
        --td-body: #344675;
        --td-light: #fdf2f8;
        --td-red: #fd5d93;
        --td-green: #00f2c3;
        --td-gray: #6c757d;
        --td-lighter: #f4f5f7;
      }
      .reveal,
      .reveal h1,
      .reveal h2,
      .reveal h3,
      .reveal h4,
      .reveal p,
      .reveal li {
        font-family: 'Geist', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
      }
      .reveal h1,
      .reveal h2,
      .reveal h3 {
        color: var(--td-dark);
        text-transform: none;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }
      .reveal h1 {
        font-size: 2.2em;
        font-weight: 800;
      }
      .reveal h2 {
        font-size: 1.5em;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-bottom: 0.4em;
      }
      .reveal h3 {
        font-size: 1.1em;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .reveal p,
      .reveal li {
        font-size: 0.65em;
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: var(--td-body);
      }
      .reveal .big-text {
        font-size: 0.8em;
        color: var(--td-dark);
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      .reveal .pain-card {
        background: #fff0f6;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--td-red);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.3em 0.6em;
        text-align: left;
        margin-bottom: 0.35em;
      }
      .reveal .pain-card p {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 0.6em;
        color: #9d174d;
      }
      .reveal .fix-card {
        background: #ecfdf5;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--td-green);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.3em 0.6em;
        text-align: left;
        margin-bottom: 0.35em;
      }
      .reveal .fix-card p {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 0.6em;
        color: #065f46;
      }
      .reveal .hero-box {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--td-dark), #2a2b4a);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 0.8em 1.2em;
        border-radius: 16px;
        margin-top: 0.4em;
      }
      .reveal .hero-box h2,
      .reveal .hero-box h3,
      .reveal .hero-box p {
        color: #fff;
      }
      .reveal .workflow-bar {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.15em;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin: 0.5em 0;
      }
      .reveal .workflow-stage {
        background: var(--td-primary);
        color: #fff;
        padding: 0.25em 0.45em;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-size: 0.5em;
        font-weight: 700;
      }
      .reveal .workflow-arrow {
        color: var(--td-primary);
        font-size: 0.6em;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        font-weight: 700;
      }
      .reveal .benefit-row {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.4em;
        background: var(--td-lighter);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.25em 0.5em;
        margin-bottom: 0.3em;
        text-align: left;
      }
      .reveal .benefit-icon {
        font-size: 1em;
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      .reveal .benefit-row p {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 0.58em;
        color: var(--td-dark);
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      .reveal .two-col {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 0.5em;
      }
      .reveal .cta-box {
        background: var(--td-light);
        border: 3px solid var(--td-primary);
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 0.7em 1em;
        margin-top: 0.5em;
      }
      .reveal section {
        padding: 0.3em;
      }
      .reveal .subtitle {
        color: var(--td-primary);
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.85em;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="slides">

        <!-- Slide 1: Title -->
        <section>
          <img src="/tailor_dost_logo_horiz.png" alt="TailorDost" style="max-height: 100px; margin: 0 auto 0.3em;" />
          <p class="subtitle">Your boutique, fully organized.</p>
          <p class="big-text" style="margin-top: 0.8em;">
            Manage orders, measurements, fabrics, photos &amp; payments
            &mdash; all in one app.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 2: Sound familiar? -->
        <section>
          <h2>Does this sound familiar?</h2>
          <div class="pain-card">
            <p>"I can't find that customer's measurements &mdash; the notebook page is torn."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pain-card">
            <p>"Which WhatsApp chat had the design photo? I've been scrolling for 10 minutes."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pain-card">
            <p>"The customer is calling again &mdash; asking if the order is ready."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pain-card">
            <p>"My tailor stitched the wrong order first because he didn't know what was urgent."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pain-card">
            <p>"Did this customer pay the full amount? I can't remember."</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 3: The cost -->
        <section>
          <h2>These small problems add up</h2>
          <p class="big-text" style="margin-top: 0.5em;">
            Lost measurements. Missed deadlines. Confused tailors.<br />
            Angry customers. Money left uncollected.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: 0.8em; font-size: 0.75em; color: var(--td-primary); font-weight: 600;">
            What if one app could fix all of this?
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 4: Introducing TailorDost -->
        <section>
          <div class="hero-box">
            <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Meet TailorDost</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75em;">
              One simple app made specifically for boutique owners like you.
              <br /><br />
              No more notebooks. No more WhatsApp searching.
              No more "is my order ready?" calls.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 5: Everything in one place -->
        <section>
          <h2>Everything in one place</h2>
          <div class="benefit-row">
            <span class="benefit-icon">&#128203;</span>
            <p>All your customers &amp; their order history</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit-row">
            <span class="benefit-icon">&#128207;</span>
            <p>Measurements saved digitally &mdash; never lost again</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit-row">
            <span class="benefit-icon">&#127912;</span>
            <p>Design photos &amp; special instructions attached to each order</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit-row">
            <span class="benefit-icon">&#129525;</span>
            <p>Fabric type, color &amp; photos &mdash; no more mix-ups</p>
          </div>
          <div class="benefit-row">
            <span class="benefit-icon">&#128176;</span>
            <p>Billing &amp; payment status &mdash; know who owes you</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 6: Track every order -->
        <section>
          <h2>Track every order, one click at a time</h2>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.2em;">Each order moves through clear stages:</p>
          <div class="workflow-bar">
            <span class="workflow-stage">Pending</span>
            <span class="workflow-arrow">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="workflow-stage">Cutting</span>
            <span class="workflow-arrow">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="workflow-stage">Stitching</span>
            <span class="workflow-arrow">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="workflow-stage">Trial Ready</span>
            <span class="workflow-arrow">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="workflow-stage">Completed</span>
            <span class="workflow-arrow">&rarr;</span>
            <span class="workflow-stage">Delivered</span>
          </div>
          <p class="big-text">
            You always know which orders are overdue<br />and what needs attention today.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 7: No more customer calls -->
        <section>
          <h2>No more "is my order ready?" calls</h2>
          <p class="big-text" style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">
            Send your customer a tracking link on WhatsApp.<br />
            They check their order status themselves.
          </p>
          <div class="fix-card">
            <p>No login needed. No app download. Just open the link and see the status.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="fix-card">
            <p>They can also see their design photos and fabric details.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="fix-card">
            <p>You control the link &mdash; set expiry or turn it off anytime.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 8: Your tailors stay on track -->
        <section>
          <h2>Your tailors stay on track</h2>
          <p class="big-text" style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">
            Share one link with your team.<br />
            They see all active orders with priorities.
          </p>
          <div class="two-col">
            <div class="fix-card">
              <p><strong>Overdue</strong> orders highlighted in red</p>
            </div>
            <div class="fix-card">
              <p><strong>Due Soon</strong> orders highlighted so they plan ahead</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p style="margin-top: 0.4em; font-size: 0.6em; color: var(--td-body);">
            No need to brief each tailor every morning.<br />
            They open the link and know exactly what to work on.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 9: Before & After -->
        <section>
          <h2>Before &amp; After TailorDost</h2>
          <div class="two-col" style="margin-top: 0.3em;">
            <div>
              <div class="pain-card"><p>Searching through notebooks</p></div>
              <div class="pain-card"><p>Scrolling WhatsApp for photos</p></div>
              <div class="pain-card"><p>Customers calling for updates</p></div>
              <div class="pain-card"><p>Tailors waiting for instructions</p></div>
              <div class="pain-card"><p>Forgetting who paid what</p></div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="fix-card"><p>Everything searchable in seconds</p></div>
              <div class="fix-card"><p>Photos attached to each order</p></div>
              <div class="fix-card"><p>Customers check status themselves</p></div>
              <div class="fix-card"><p>Tailors see priorities on their own</p></div>
              <div class="fix-card"><p>Payment status always up to date</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 10: Your data is safe -->
        <section>
          <h2>Your data is 100% safe</h2>
          <p class="big-text">
            Only you can see your customers and orders.<br />
            Bank-level security. No one else has access.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 11: CTA -->
        <section>
          <h2>Ready to organize your boutique?</h2>
          <div class="cta-box">
            <h3 style="color: var(--td-primary); margin-top: 0;">Start using TailorDost today</h3>
            <p class="big-text">
              Simple to use. Made for boutique owners.<br />
              Your orders, measurements, photos &amp; payments &mdash; all in one place.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>

    <script is:inline src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/reveal.js@5.1.0/dist/reveal.js"></script>
    <script is:inline>
      Reveal.initialize({
        controls: true,
        progress: true,
        slideNumber: false,
        hash: false,
        transition: "slide",
        center: true,
        width: 960,
        height: 700,
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
